article.headline: Cornell 67, Harvard 63
article.story: BOSTON (AP) --Ryan Rourke scored a career high 27 points and pulled down 10 rebounds on Saturday to lead Cornell to a 67-63 win over Harvard. Jason Canady had 15 points and Eric Taylor added 10 points for Cornell. Kevin Rogus led Harvard with 23 points while Matt Stehle and Brian Cusworth each had 10. Cornell (11-12, 6-4 Ivy League) trailed 26-22 at halftime but opened the second half with a 6-0 run to tie the score at 28-28 on Cody Toppert's jump shot with 16:54 to play. The Big Red pulled ahead by as many as seven points in the second half. But Matt Stehle scored two free throws with 5:24 remaining in the game as Harvard (10-13, 5-5) cut Cornell's lead to 48-46. The Big Red answered with a 7-1 run to take a 56-47 lead on Canady's jumper with 3:22 left.
